  "description": "Solanaceae herb from tropical Amazon (southern Brazil to Bolivia). Produces intensely pungent fruit with floral/fruity volatiles. Includes habanero, Scotch bonnet, and datil cultivars. Misnomer \"chinense\" reflects 18th-century European misconception of Chinese origin; domestication evidence points to Caribbean and tropical South America.",
